title: Measurement of fission neutron spectrum averaged cross sections of some threshold reactions on nickel: small scale production of Co-57 in a nuclear reactor

x4freetext: Measurement of fission neutron spectrum averaged cross
sections of some threshold reactions on nickel: small
scale production of Co-57 in a nuclear reactor
Enriched Ni-58 powder (99.66%) or Ni-foil (0.1 mm
thick, 99.99% pure) each weighing 25 to 100 mg, was
sealed in a quartz ampoule, studded with neutron flux
monitor foils and then placed in an nrx type
The fast neutron flux densities, effective at the
ampoules, were determined using the first three monitor
threshold reactions. The thermal flux density was
determined via the last two reactions.
